{
  "doc_id": "19428",
  "text": "In many retrieval methods, the surface-level similarity of a document to a query is an important source of information in estimating the relevance of the document to the underlying information need. Over the Web, this \"relevance indicator\" can be highly misleading due to the adversarial and noisy nature of the retrieval setting; e.g., search engine optimization (SEO) efforts that employ content manipulation [CITATION_1] can significantly bias relevance estimates that are based on surface level document-query similarities.",
